This endpoint allows you to upload images using base64 encoding and receive real-time streaming analysis.

### Request Body

<ParamField body="model" type="string" required>
  The model ID (e.g., `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4o-mini`, `claude-3-5-sonnet-20240620`).
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="messages" type="array" required>
  The conversation history. For images, use the following structure:
  
  ```json
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": [
      { "type": "text", "text": "What is in this image?" },
      {
        "type": "image_url",
        "image_url": {
          "url": "data:image/jpeg;base64,{BASE64_ENCODED_IMAGE}"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="stream" type="boolean" default="true">
  Must be set to `true` for streaming responses.
</ParamField>

### Response

The response is a stream of [Chat Completion Chunk Objects](/Chat/ChatGpt%20interface/ChatGPT%20(Chat)/chat-completion-block-object).
